result.execSummary:
The defendant William S. Dahl was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation, Domestic Abuse (Waushara County Case No. 2015CF67) [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Felony Bail Jumping (Waushara Co Case No. 2015CF142), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Possession of Tetrahydrocannabinols (THC) (Waushara County Case No. 2017CF147), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Burglary of a Building or Dwelling, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime (Waupaca County Case No. 2017CF169) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.
Defendant is not to be in possession of any dangerous weapons, including any firearms.
